    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 13 @ 2021/2022",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Semiconductors partly conduct and partly insulate. Examples are, except",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "Silicon",
        "Tungsten",
        "Germanium",
        "Gallium Arsenide (GaAs)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Tungsten"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Semiconductors are materials that have a conductivity between conductors and insulators, such as Silicon, Germanium, and Gallium Arsenide (GaAs), which is why Tungsten is the correct answer (as the exception). Tungsten is a metal and a good conductor, not a semiconductor. Silicon, Germanium, and GaAs are all well-known semiconductors used in electronics due to their intermediate conductivity and ability to be doped. Thus, Tungsten does not belong to this group."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Semiconductors",
      "Conductors",
      "Electric Current"
    ]
